  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency assistance to re-establish agriculture and livelihoods of households affected by Tropical Cyclone Harold</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to restore food security and livelihoods for Cyclone-affected agricultural households.  FAO will use CERF funds to provide agricultural inputs (seeds, tools and/or other local planting materials) and train households on processing and conserving vegetables among other activities.  Over 30,000 people will benefit from this project, which will be implemented within 6 months.</narrative>
  </description>
